verbose_text: F1.2 levels slightly increased in the rivaroxaban group from baseline to end of treatment, which was significantly different from the VKA treatment arm, in which F1.2 levels decreased (rivaroxaban : 2.7% [95% confidence interval (CI) : -5.6 to 11.7%]; VKA : -53% [95% CI : -58.1 to -47.3%]; p < 0.001).
